'''Ri̱pobi̱lik Di̱mokrasi Konggo''', '''RD Konggo''' (Fi̱ransa: République démocratique du Congo (RDC) [kɔ̃ɡo]), á̱niet ma a̱di̱di̱t ngyei '''Konggo-Kinshasa''', ku '''A̱gba̱ndang Konggo'''), a̱wot á̱ ku ngyei '''Zayir''' gbangbang a̱ni, yet a̱byin kya di̱ fam-a̱byin A̱ka̱wa̱tyia̱ Afrika. It is, by area, the second largest country in Africa (after Algeria), and the 11th-largest in the world. With a population of around 108 million, the Democratic Republic of the Congo is the most populous officially Francophone country in the world. It is a member of the United Nations, Non-Aligned Movement, African Union, COMESA, South African Development Community, and the East African Community. The capital and largest city is Kinshasa, which is also the world's most populous Francophone city and largest city in Africa. It is the third largest city in metropolitan area after Lagos and Cairo.
